race.description: The Sporting Globe After The Last Handicap (Bm78)
race.comment: BIG SEXY (11) is up to 1400m here second up but has plenty of ability and the profile to match, winning dominantly at Hamilton as favourite having shown good ability last time in. Beaten just 2.3 lengths at Flemington over this trip at his second career start, he looks set to measure up against opposition that have largely found their mark. ACTIVE DUTY (6) is racing well. He was far too good when last seen at Ballarat over 1600m. Back in trip here is of some concern but expect they roll forward and try to make this a stern test. RUSSIAN METEOR (4) was solid fresh at Seymour with 61.5kg and should be fitter. IMPENDING LINK (7) was just fair in the same race but had been going well prior and can bounce back.
